# Obsolete Code Cleanup (Mandatory)

- When implementing or refactoring features, remove replaced or unused code paths immediately.
- Do not keep legacy UI flows, dead handlers, deprecated state fields, or temporary fallback branches unless explicitly required.
- If old logic is still needed for compatibility, document the reason in the same change.
- Keep i18n keys, API payload fields, and menu items aligned with active behavior; delete orphaned entries.
- Keep token/schema renames clean: remove deprecated alias fields after call sites are migrated.
- Prefer clear deletion over commented-out code.

## Example

```text
BAD: Keep old right-click menu code after adding a new menu implementation.
GOOD: Remove old menu trigger/handler and keep only one active path.
```
